description:
On June 30, 2020, the Cape Verdean government has introduced a de-confinement plan for the whole country which includes the ongoing civic duty to stay at home, except:
- to buy food or other essential times;
- to go to work if unable to work from home;
- to go to hospital or health centres;
- to carry out caring or similar duties or in case of real need;
- to exercise outdoors and at some facilities and to walk pets.
